<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Phase 21 - suite-level timeout guardrail.

  The integration suite normally finishes in seconds (full solution ~6 s, integration
  project ~5 s cold / ~2 s warm). A regression once produced a 21m43s run whose root
  cause was environmental (a per-construction Release publish in CliBinaryFixture, since
  removed - see plan/DONE/PHASE-21-test-suite-performance.md).

  Per-test CancellationTokenSource timeouts (30 s / 60 s / 120 s) already make an
  individual stalled test fail fast. This is the COMPLEMENTARY suite-level cap: if the
  whole session ever hangs (a regression no per-test timeout catches, e.g. fixture setup
  or process-spawn contention), VSTest aborts the run and FAILS it in bounded time
  instead of silently eating 20+ minutes.

  TestSessionTimeout is in milliseconds. 300000 = 5 minutes: ~50x the normal full-suite
  runtime (generous slack for cold CI machines, native-binary AV scanning, and cache
  misses) yet well under the 21-minute pathological case it exists to catch. This matches
  the value already referenced by plan/PHASE-30-cross-platform-ci.md.

  Apply by passing this file via the dotnet test "settings" option.
-->
<RunSettings>
  <RunConfiguration>
    <TestSessionTimeout>300000</TestSessionTimeout>
  </RunConfiguration>
</RunSettings>
